Here’s the narrative of the scene in “The Wolf of Wallstreet” as given by Jordan Belfort. If you’re selling to a customer, it’s important to make a personal connection and make your customer feel like you (the expert) knows exactly what they need, thus providing them with the product that fits their needs.
Could you sell Jordan a pen?

Challenge your schedule and ask yourself if you're effective are you mostly tocusing on the things you have" to do or the things you're" Caed' to do? A Presented by @businessfact.in Idea @businessfact.in'.

Photo by Entrepreneurship | Business on September 04, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'BusinessFact.in 3.Having Empathy You can be the most disciplined, brilliant, and even wealthy individual in the world, but if you don't care for a empathize with other people, then you are basically nothing but a sociopath," ~Kamia Taylor Presented by @businessfact.in Idea @businessfact.in'.

Photo by Entrepreneurship | Business on September 04, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'BusinessFact.in 4.Positive Self- Talk It doesn't matter what others think of you, but what you think of yourself certainly does~and. It takes time to build that level of confidence and ability to believe in yourself when nobody else does. Presented by @businessfact.in Idea @businessfact.in'.

Photo by Entrepreneurship | Business on September 04, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'BusinessFact.in 5.Being Honest With Yourself What ever you are doing, you must be brutally honest with yourself, especially in business. Always know that you compete with no one; run your own race. know what you know and also be aware of what you do not know. Just focus on being good at what you do. A Presented by @businessfact.in Idea @businessfact.in'.

Photo by Entrepreneurship | Business on September 04, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'BusinessFact.in 6. Stop Whining We must learn to stop whining about what will happen, what will never happen, what we have and do not have, what somebody did or didn't do. Practice a life of no whining, no criticizing, and no complaining. N Presented by @businessfact.in Idea @businessfact.in'.

Photo by Entrepreneurship | Business on September 04, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'BusinessFact.in 7. Focus On The Present moment Being in the present moment is where you will have the greatest control, where you will feel the most at ease, and where happiness flourishes. There is a super tight connection between happiness and the ability to live in the present moment. Staying present is the skills of having your mind in the moment, not in the past, not in the future, but right here. Presented by @businessfact.in Idea @businessfact.in'.

Photo by Entrepreneurship | Business on September 04, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'BusinessFact.in 8. Being Consistent Life is a journey, Success is not a one time action but a continuous process. There is no time to mourn over your failures because this waste time, but just pick yourself up and keep moving on. Success is not a destination, but buta a process of consistency is a journey. Presented by @businessfact.in Idea @businessfact.in'.
